{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0185gto1ZBRwFGBzNzZ2nsZU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"total_count\":12,\"incomplete_results\":false,\"items\":[{\"id\":3526644269,\"number\":14,\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"title\":\"Daily Test Coverage Improver - Signal.PeakDetection Module Tests\",\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAdded comprehensive test coverage for the **Signal.PeakDetection** module, achieving **82% line coverage** and **72% branch coverage** for a previously untested signal processing module. This PR adds **25 new test cases** covering peak detection, valley detection, and related utility functions.\\n\\n## Problems Found\\n\\nThe `Signal/PeakDetection` module had **0% test coverage** despite providing essential signal processing functionality:\\n- Local maxima and minima detection for peak finding in noisy data\\n- Index-based peak location functions\\n- Peak labeling with extrema classification\\n- Helper functions for iterating and identifying peaks\\n- Peak feature creation utilities\\n\\n## Actions Taken\\n\\n### 1. Local Maxima Detection Tests (5 test cases)\\n- **Single peak detection**: Tests finding one peak in simple data with proper concavity\\n- **Multiple peaks detection**: Validates finding multiple peaks in a signal\\n- **Threshold respect**: Tests that yThreshold parameter filters peaks correctly\\n- **Empty array handling**: Validates return of empty array for data with â‰¤5 points\\n- **Index-based detection**: Tests `localMaximaIdx` returning indices instead of values\\n\\n### 2. Local Minima Detection Tests (5 test cases)\\n- **Single valley detection**: Tests finding one minimum in simple data\\n- **Multiple minima detection**: Validates finding multiple valleys in a signal\\n- **Empty array handling**: Tests behavior with small datasets\\n- **Index-based detection**: Tests `localMinimaIdx` returning indices\\n\\n### 3. Peak Location Functions (6 test cases)\\n- **idxOfHighestPeakBy**: Tests finding highest of two flanking peaks\\n  - Target before first value\\n  - Target after last value\\n  - Target between values\\n- **idxOfClosestPeakBy**: Tests finding nearest peak to a target x-value\\n  - Exact match\\n  - Closest approximation  \\n  - Empty array handling\\n\\n### 4. Peak Labeling Tests (3 test cases)\\n- **Dual labeling**: Tests labelPeaks identifying both positive and negative extrema\\n- **Edge point handling**: Validates that first/last 3 points are labeled as None\\n- **Empty array handling**: Tests behavior with small datasets\\n\\n### 5. Utility Function Tests (4 test cases)\\n- **iterUntil**: Tests forward and backward iteration with predicate\\n  - Forward search\\n  - Backward search\\n  - Boundary conditions (reaching start/end)\\n- **iterUntili**: Tests iteration with index-aware predicate\\n- **createPeakFeature**: Tests peak feature record creation\\n\\n## Test Coverage Results\\n\\n### PeakDetection Module (Signal/PeakDetection.fs)\\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Line Coverage** | 0/142 (0.0%) | **112/142 (82.0%)** | **+112 lines (+82.0 pp)** |\\n| **Branch Coverage** | 0% | **72.0%** | **+72.0 pp** |\\n\\n### Overall Project Coverage\\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| **Total Tests** | 1,630 | **1,655** | **+25 tests** |\\n| **Line Coverage** | 38.53% | 38.98% | +0.45 pp |\\n| **Methods Covered** | 3,936/10,679 | 3,981/10,710 | +45 methods |\\n| **Classes Covered** | 2,595/4,291 | 2,629/4,322 | +34 classes |\\n| **Branches Covered** | 4,721/32,390 | 4,815/32,421 | +94 branches |\\n\\nAll 1,655 tests pass successfully.\\n\\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n```bash\\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\\ndotnet tool restore\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"Before\\\" Coverage Baseline\\n```bash\\n# From main branch\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Generate \\\"After\\\" Coverage (with new tests)\\n```bash\\n# After applying this PR\\ngit checkout test-coverage/peak-detection-1760715536\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\\\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n```\\n\\n### Run Only New PeakDetection Tests\\n```bash\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\\\\n  --configuration Release \\\\\\n  --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~PeakDetection\\\"\\n```\\n\\nExpected output: **25 new tests passing**\\n\\n### Analyze Coverage for PeakDetection Module\\n```python\\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\\n\\ndef get_peak_detection_coverage(filename):\\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\\n    root = tree.getroot()\\n    for pkg in root.findall('.//package'):\\n        if pkg.get('name') != 'FSharp.Stats':\\n            continue\\n        for cls in pkg.findall('.//class'):\\n            fname = cls.get('filename', '')\\n            if 'Signal/PeakDetection.fs' not in fname or '/Tests/' in fname:\\n                continue\\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\\n            total = len(lines)\\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) \\u003e 0)\\n            line_rate = float(cls.get('line-rate', 0))\\n            return covered, total, line_rate * 100\\n    return 0, 0, 0.0\\n\\nbefore = get_peak_detection_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\\nafter = get_peak_detection_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\\n\\nprint(f\\\"BEFORE: {before[0]}/{before[1]} lines ({before[2]:.1f}%)\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"AFTER:  {after[0]}/{after[1]} lines ({after[2]:.1f}%)\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"IMPROVEMENT: +{after[0] - before[0]} lines (+{after[2] - before[2]:.1f} pp)\\\")\\n```\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\nThese tests were designed to:\\n- **Validate peak detection algorithms**: Ensure correct identification of local maxima and minima\\n- **Test concavity requirements**: Verify the algorithm checks i-2, i-1, i, i+1, i+2 for proper peak shape\\n- **Handle edge cases**: Small datasets (â‰¤5 points), empty arrays, boundary conditions\\n- **Test threshold filtering**: Validate yThreshold parameter works correctly  \\n- **Verify utility functions**: Test iteration and helper functions used by peak detection\\n- **Cover both value and index APIs**: Test functions returning (x,y) tuples vs indices\\n\\n## Background on Peak Detection\\n\\nThe PeakDetection module implements algorithms for finding local extrema in signals:\\n- **Local Maxima/Minima**: Identifies peaks/valleys by checking that a point is greater/less than its neighbors\\n- **Concavity Check**: Validates trend over 5-point window (i-2 to i+2) to avoid noise artifacts\\n- **Threshold Filtering**: Allows filtering peaks below a minimum height\\n- **Labeling System**: Classifies points as Positive extrema, Negative extrema, or None\\n- **Helper Functions**: Provides iteration and search utilities for working with peak data\\n\\nThe algorithms are sensitive to noise, which is why they check trends over multiple points and why integration with smoothing (e.g., Savitzky-Golay) is recommended for noisy signals.\\n\\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\\n\\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\\n1. **Signal Processing** modules:\\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Baseline correction (66 lines, 0% coverage)  \\n   - QQPlot (84 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - ContinuousWavelet (48 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Padding (60 lines, 0% coverage)\\n2. **SecondDerivative submodule** within PeakDetection:\\n   - Peak characterization functions (currently untested)\\n   - Peak end detection (borders and convolution)\\n   - Full peak identification pipeline (getPeaks function)\\n3. **Linear Algebra**:\\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - LinearAlgebraServiceMKL (406 lines, 0% coverage)\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eCommands and Searches Performed\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n### Bash Commands\\n```bash\\n# Coverage analysis\\npython3 /tmp/gh-aw/agent/analyze_coverage.py codeCov.xml\\npython3 /tmp/gh-aw/agent/compare_peakdetection_coverage.py\\n\\n# Branch creation\\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/peak-detection-1760715536\\n\\n# Source code inspection\\ncat src/FSharp.Stats/Signal/PeakDetection.fs\\n\\n# Build and test\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~PeakDetection\\\"\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release\\n\\n# Coverage generation\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build \\\\\\n  /p:AltCover=true /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml /p:AltCoverForce=true\\n\\n# Git operations\\ngit add tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Signal.fs\\ngit commit -m \\\"Add comprehensive tests for Signal.PeakDetection module...\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### Web Searches\\nNone performed - relied on existing project structure, coverage reports, and signal processing knowledge.\\n\\n### Web Pages Fetched\\nNone - all information gathered from local repository files and coverage reports.\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n---\\n\\nðŸ¤– Generated by Daily Test Coverage Improver Agent\\n\\n\\n\\u003e AI generated by [Daily Test Coverage Improver](https://github.com/githubnext/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/actions/runs/18597483964)\",\"author_association\":\"CONTRIBUTOR\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"github-actions[bot]\",\"id\":41898282,\"node_id\":\"MDM6Qm90NDE