getroot()\\n    for cls in root.findall('.//class'):\\n        fname = cls.get('filename', '')\\n        if 'Optimization/BrentExt.fs' in fname or 'Optimization\\\\\\\\BrentExt.fs' in fname:\\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\\n            total = len(lines)\\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) \\u003e 0)\\n            print(f\\\"{fname}: {covered}/{total} lines ({covered/total*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"BEFORE:\\\")\\nget_brent_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nAFTER:\\\")\\nget_brent_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\\n```\\n\\nExpected output:\\n```\\nBEFORE:\\nBrentExt.fs: 0/120 lines (0.0%)\\n\\nAFTER:\\nBrentExt.fs: 120/120 lines (100.0%)\\n```\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\nThese tests were designed to:\\n- **Validate algorithmic correctness**: Ensure Brent's method finds minima/maxima accurately for various function types\\n- **Test convergence properties**: Verify the algorithm converges for well-behaved functions\\n- **Cover edge cases**: Boundaries, narrow intervals, reversed bounds, non-smooth functions\\n- **Test error handling**: Validate proper exception throwing for invalid inputs\\n- **Verify numerical stability**: Test with different function types (polynomial, trigonometric, exponential)\\n- **Test customization**: Validate custom tolerance and iteration limits\\n- **Maximize and minimize**: Test both optimization directions\\n\\n## Background on Brent's Method\\n\\nBrent's method is a sophisticated optimization algorithm that combines:\\n- **Golden section search**: Reliable fallback ensuring convergence\\n- **Parabolic interpolation**: Faster convergence when the function is smooth near the minimum\\n\\nThe algorithm intelligently switches between these methods to ensure both:\\n1. **Guaranteed convergence** (through golden section fallback)\\n2. **Fast convergence** (when parabolic interpolation is applicable)\\n\\nThis makes Brent's method one of the most reliable and efficient univariate optimization algorithms, widely used in scientific computing.\\n\\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\\n\\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\\n1. **Signal Processing** modules (0% coverage in many):\\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - PeakDetection (142+ lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Baseline correction and filtering\\n2. **Linear Algebra**:\\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - LinearAlgebraServiceMKL (406 lines, 0% coverage)\\n3. **Distributions**:\\n   - Bandwidth selection (110 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - KernelDensity (80 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - Various continuous distributions\\n4. **Other Optimization/Fitting**:\\n   - NonLinearRegression (148 lines, 0% coverage)\\n   - GoodnessOfFit (94 lines, 0% coverage)\\n5. **Interpolation**:\\n   - Interpolation module (104 lines, 0% coverage)\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eCommands and Searches Performed\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n### Bash Commands\\n```bash\\n# Coverage analysis\\ntail -100 coverage-steps.log\\npython3 (parse coverage XML and find low-coverage modules)\\npython3 (filter to FSharp.Stats files only)\\n\\n# Branch creation\\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/brent-optimization-1760713575\\n\\n# Source code inspection\\n# Read: src/FSharp.Stats/Optimization/BrentExt.fs\\n# Read: tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Optimization.fs\\n\\n# Build and test\\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --filter \\\"FullyQualifiedName~Optimization.Brent\\\" --no-build\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build\\n\\n# Test debugging and fixing\\ndotnet fsi /tmp/gh-aw/agent/test_brent3.fsx\\npython3 (mathematical verification of test expectations)\\n\\n# Coverage generation\\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build /p:AltCover=true