{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_01XzY7Ch21urpDFmFxJir8ZZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017p4xNf35ENEeCj5jJJm7b4","name":"mcp__safe_outputs__create_pull_request","input":{"branch":"test-coverage/interpolation-linearspline-step-1760716548","title":"Daily Test Coverage Improver - Interpolation.LinearSpline and Step Modules Tests","body":"## Summary\n\nAdded comprehensive test coverage for the **Interpolation.LinearSpline** and **Interpolation.Step** modules, achieving **83.9% line coverage** for LinearSpline and **64.3% line coverage** for Step, both previously undertested interpolation modules. This PR adds **27 new test cases** covering linear spline and step function interpolation.\n\n## Problems Found\n\nThe `Interpolation.LinearSpline` and `Interpolation.Step` modules had low test coverage despite providing essential interpolation functionality:\n\n### LinearSpline Module (12.9% â†’ 83.9% coverage)\n- Linear spline interpolation using straight lines between knots\n- Derivative calculation capabilities\n- Support for sorted and unsorted data\n- In-place sorting options\n- Only 8/62 lines were covered before these tests\n\n### Step Module (46.4% â†’ 64.3% coverage)\n- Step function interpolation with horizontal steps between knots\n- Derivative calculation (always zero for step functions)\n- Support for sorted and unsorted data\n- Only partial coverage existed\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n### 1. LinearSpline Tests (15 test cases)\n\n**Basic Interpolation Tests** (3 tests):\n- Simple linear data with uniform spacing\n- Non-uniform data spacing\n- Unsorted data handling\n\n**Extrapolation Tests** (2 tests):\n- Extrapolation beyond upper bound (uses last segment slope)\n- Extrapolation below lower bound (uses first segment slope)\n\n**Derivative Tests** (3 tests):\n- Constant slope scenarios\n- Varying slopes (piecewise linear approximation of xÂ²)\n- Member functions (`Differentiate()` and `getDerivative()`)\n\n**Edge Cases** (2 tests):\n- In-place array modification behavior\n- Two-point interpolation (minimum valid case)\n\n**Error Handling** (5 tests):\n- Array length mismatch detection\n- Insufficient data points (single point)\n- Validation for all interpolation variants\n\n### 2. Step Function Tests (12 test cases)\n\n**Basic Step Function Tests** (2 tests):\n- Basic step behavior (returns left value between knots)\n- Unsorted data handling\n\n**Extrapolation Tests** (2 tests):\n- Extrapolation beyond upper bound (returns last value)\n- Extrapolation below lower bound (returns first value)\n\n**Derivative Tests** (3 tests):\n- Derivative is always zero (step functions are constant except at discontinuities)\n- Member functions (`Differentiate()` and `getDerivative()`)\n\n**Edge Cases** (2 tests):\n- Single point interpolation\n- Two-point interpolation\n\n**Error Handling** (3 tests):\n- Array length mismatch detection for both variants\n\n## Test Coverage Results\n\n### LinearSpline Module (Interpolation/LinearSpline.fs)\n| Class | Before | After | Improvement |\n|-------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **LinearSpline** | 8/50 (16.0%) | **42/50 (84.0%)** | **+34 lines (+68.0 pp)** |\n| **LinearSplineCoef** | 0/8 (0.0%) | **6/8 (75.0%)** | **+6 lines (+75.0 pp)** |\n| **get_Predict@376-2** | 0/4 (0.0%) | **4/4 (100.0%)** | **+4 lines (+100.0 pp)** |\n| **TOTAL** | **8/62 (12.9%)** | **52/62 (83.9%)** | **+44 lines (+71.0 pp)** |\n\n### Step Module (Interpolation/Step.fs)\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **Step (interpolation)** | 0/30 (0.0%) | **26/30 (86.7%)** | **+26 lines (+86.7 pp)** |\n| **StepCoef** | 0/6 (0.0%) | **2/6 (33.3%)** | **+2 lines (+33.3 pp)** |\n| **get_Predict@619-3** | 0/2 (0.0%) | **2/2 (100.0%)** | **+2 lines (+100.0 pp)** |\n| **TOTAL** | **78/168 (46.4%)** | **108/168 (64.3%)** | **+30 lines (+17.9 pp)** |\n\nNote: The Step module total includes other unrelated classes that share the \"Step\" name.\n\n### Overall Project Coverage\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------| \n| **Total Tests** | 1,655 | **1,681** | **+26 tests** |\n| **Line Coverage** | 38.98% | 39.31% | **+0.33 pp** |\n| **Methods Covered** | 3,981/10,710 | 4,026/10,742 | **+45 methods** |\n| **Classes Covered** | 2,629/4,322 | 2,666/4,354 | **+37 classes** |\n| **Branches Covered** | 4,815/32,421 | 4,836/32,453 | **+21 branches** |\n\nAll 1,681 tests pass successfully.\n\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\n\n### Prerequisites\n```bash\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\ndotnet tool restore\n```\n\n### Generate \"Before\" Coverage Baseline\n```bash\n# From main branch\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Generate \"After\" Coverage (with new tests)\n```bash\n# After applying this PR\ngit checkout test-coverage/interpolation-linearspline-step-1760716548\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Run Only New Interpolation Tests\n```bash\n# LinearSpline tests\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~LinearSpline\"\n\n# Step tests\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~Step\"\n```\n\nExpected output: **27 new tests passing** (15 LinearSpline + 12 Step)\n\n### Analyze Coverage for Interpolation Modules\n```python\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n\ndef get_module_coverage(filename, module_name):\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\n    root = tree.getroot()\n    \n    for pkg in root.findall('.//package'):\n        for cls in pkg.findall('.//class'):\n            classname = cls.get('name', '')\n            if module_name in classname:\n                lines = cls.findall('.//line')\n                covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', '0')) > 0)\n                total = len(lines)\n                print(f\"{classname}: {covered}/{total} ({covered/total*100:.1f}%)\")\n\nprint(\"BEFORE:\")\nget_module_coverage('codeCov_before.xml', 'LinearSpline')\nget_module_coverage('codeCov_before.xml', 'Step')\n\nprint(\"\\nAFTER:\")\nget_module_coverage('codeCov_after.xml', 'LinearSpline')\nget_module_coverage('codeCov_after.xml', 'Step')\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\nThese tests were designed to:\n- **Validate interpolation correctness**: Ensure linear splines and step functions produce correct values at knots and between knots\n- **Test extrapolation behavior**: Validate behavior outside the input range\n- **Cover derivative calculations**: Verify slope calculations for linear splines and zero derivatives for step functions\n- **Test data handling**: Validate sorting, in-place modification, and data validation\n- **Handle edge cases**: Minimum data sizes, boundary conditions\n- **Verify error handling**: Validate proper exception throwing for invalid inputs\n- **Test member vs. static functions**: Ensure both APIs work correctly\n\n## Background on Linear Splines and Step Functions\n\n### LinearSpline\nLinear spline interpolation connects data points with straight line segments:\n- **Simple and fast**: Computationally efficient\n- **Continuous**: Function is continuous but not smooth (first derivative is discontinuous)\n- **Local**: Each segment depends only on neighboring points\n- **Derivative**: Piecewise constant (slope of each linear segment)\n- Used when simple interpolation is sufficient and smoothness is not required\n\n### Step Functions\nStep functions are piecewise constant:\n- **Simplest interpolation**: Returns the value at the nearest left data point\n- **Discontinuous**: Jumps at each data point\n- **Zero derivative**: Derivative is zero everywhere except at discontinuities\n- **Left-continuous**: Returns left value between points\n- Used for discrete data, histograms, and when maintaining constant values between measurements\n\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\n\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\n1. **Polynomial interpolation derivatives and integrals**:\n   - `Polynomial.differentiate` (0% coverage)\n   - `Polynomial.integrate` (0% coverage)\n   - `Polynomial.getDerivative` (0% coverage)\n   - `Polynomial.getIntegralBetween` (0% coverage)\n2. **CubicSpline.Hermite** submodule (0/104 lines, 0% coverage):\n   - Hermite cubic spline interpolation with custom slopes\n   - More complex than standard cubic splines\n3. **Signal Processing** modules:\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Baseline correction (66 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Padding (60 lines, 0% coverage)\n4. **Other Interpolation**:\n   - Approximation module (0/30 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Various CubicSpline boundary conditions\n\n<details>\n<summary>Commands and Searches Performed</summary>\n\n### Bash Commands\n```bash\n# Coverage analysis\ntail -100 coverage-steps.log\npython3 (analyze coverage XML for low-coverage modules)\npython3 (filter to FSharp.Stats files only)\npython3 (detailed coverage analysis for LinearSpline and Step)\nwc -l src/FSharp.Stats/Interpolation.fs\ngrep -E \"^\\s*(module |let |type )\" src/FSharp.Stats/Interpolation.fs | head -80\n\n# Branch creation\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/interpolation-linearspline-step-1760716548\n\n# Build and test\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~LinearSpline\"\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~Step\"\n\n# Coverage generation\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true /p:AltCoverCobertura=../../codeCov_after.xml /p:AltCoverForce=true\n\n# Coverage comparison\npython3 (compare before/after coverage for LinearSpline and Step modules)\npython3 (get overall project coverage statistics)\n\n# Formatting\ndotnet fantomas tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Interpolation.fs\n\n# Git operations\ngit add tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Interpolation.fs\ngit commit -m \"Add comprehensive tests for Interpolation.LinearSpline and Step modules...\"\n```\n\n### Web Searches\nNone performed - relied on existing project structure, coverage reports, and interpolation theory knowledge.\n\n### Web Pages Fetched\nNone - all information gathered from local repository files, coverage reports, and mathematical understanding of interpolation methods.\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\nðŸ¤– Generated by Daily Test Coverage Improver Agent"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":423,"cache_read_input_tokens":139551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":423,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64567296-8fda-47f8-9f77-bf23343177ff","uuid":"f0ddceba-340a-4723-8300-8c8f0e6fb47a"}
